abstract: >-
  Reference implementation for Boundary-Condition Quantum Mechanics IV_d
  (BCQM IV_d). Simulates bundles of soft-rudder primitive threads, with
  optional shared-bias glue, to study how centre-of-mass inertial noise
  scales with the coherence horizon W_coh and bundle size N. Includes the
  A-series (single-thread regression and independent bundles) and B-series
  (shared-bias bundles) runs, analysis tools, and figure-generation scripts.
